\fs28 \cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 Innovation isn\'92t just happening in Silicon Valley. It\'92s happening everywhere. \uc0\u55356 \u57103 \cb1 \
\
\cb3 At our recent TiE Singapore\'96Endeavor Catalyst session, \'93What the Ecosystem Needs: Propelling the SEA Ecosystem to the Next Level\'94, one thing became clear: the global startup story is more distributed than we think.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 Over the last decade, most unicorns have emerged outside traditional hubs, from Asia to Latin America, Europe, and the Middle East. What\'92s driving this shift? Founders tackling local problems at scale, capital ecosystems that are maturing rapidly, and entrepreneurs thinking global from day one.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 The conversation highlighted that while traditional innovation hubs still matter, real scale, meaningful impact, and returns are increasingly happening in new geographies including Southeast Asia.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 \uc0\u55357 \u56593  Key takeaways:\cb1 \
\cb3 \uc0\u9643 \u65039  Innovation starts locally but is built to scale globally\cb1 \
\cb3 \uc0\u9643 \u65039  Capital is flowing beyond traditional hubs, creating new growth corridors\cb1 \
\cb3 \uc0\u9643 \u65039  Founders are launching global-first companies from day one\cb1 \
\cb3 \uc0\u9643 \u65039  Talent, ambition, and opportunity no longer have borders\cb1 \
\cb3 \uc0\u9643 \u65039  Southeast Asia is becoming a builder ecosystem, not just a consumer market\cb1 \
\
