\fs28 \cf5 \cb3 \strokec5 Back in times, supplier onboarding used to be a formality, but today, it\'92s one of the biggest silent taxes in finance. This is not because the process changed but because everything around it did.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 CFOs are closing faster, running leaner teams, and tightening governance. \cb1 \
\cb3 When onboarding is slow or error-prone, every downstream workflow suffers. P2P slows, rework increases, controls weaken, and working capital stays stuck.\cb1 \
\
\cb3 What CFOs actually need is execution:\cb1 \
\cb3  \'95 Real-time validation, not post-facto cleanup\cb1 \
\cb3  \'95 Compliance checked before a vendor enters the system\cb1 \
\cb3  \'95 One source of truth across ERP, procurement, tax, and payments\cb1 \
\cb3  \'95 Audit-ready traceability from day one\cb1 \
\
\cb3 This is where AI changes the game, especially when combined with domain expertise. Not just automation, but a cleaner, predictable P2P foundation. That\'92s exactly what we build at Neoflo.\cb1 \
\
